                            <p class="mb-4">In Java, a <code class="bg-white/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-md text-sm text-yellow-300">for</code> loop is used for iterating over arrays and collections.</p>
                            <p class="mb-4">Your task is to write a simple program that calculates the sum of all numbers in a given array. Use a <code class="bg-white/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-md text-sm text-yellow-300">for</code> loop to iterate through the array and accumulate the total.</p>
                            <div class="bg-background-dark p-4 rounded-lg my-6">
<pre class="text-sm"><code class="language-java"><span class="text-blue-400">public class</span> <span class="text-yellow-300">Main</span> {
    <span class="text-blue-400">public static void</span> <span class="text-yellow-300">main</span>(<span class="text-purple-400">String</span>[] <span class="text-orange-400">args</span>) {
        <span class="text-blue-400">int</span>[] <span class="text-purple-400">numbers</span> = {<span class="text-green-300">10</span>, <span class="text-green-300">20</span>, <span class="text-green-300">30</span>, <span class="text-green-300">40</span>, <span class="text-green-300">50</span>};
        <span class="text-blue-400">int</span> <span class="text-purple-400">totalSum</span> = <span class="text-green-300">0</span>;
        <span class="text-gray-500">// Your code here</span>
        <span class="text-purple-400">System</span>.<span class="text-purple-400">out</span>.<span class="text-yellow-300">println</span>(<span class="text-green-300">"The sum is: " + totalSum</span>);
    }
}</code></pre>
